## Summary

| Step | Result |
|---|---|
| Pre-check existing indexes | Only `orders_pkey` on `id` — no duplicate risk |
| Index creation method | `CREATE INDEX CONCURRENTLY` — zero write blocking |
| Lock type acquired | `ShareUpdateExclusiveLock` (non-blocking to INSERTs/UPDATEs/DELETEs) |
| Build time | ~180 seconds |
| Index verified | ✅ `idx_orders_user_id` B-Tree on `orders(user_id)` |
| Residual locks | None |

The `user_id` B-Tree index is live. Queries filtering or joining on `user_id` will now hit the index instead of doing full sequential scans on 500M rows. The DBA team should see query times drop from 10s+ to milliseconds for typical `user_id` lookups.

**Rollback plan** (if ever needed): `DROP INDEX CONCURRENTLY idx_orders_user_id;` — also non-blocking.
